Photo: Jabulani Langa“It’s true he instructed me to look for the land for Mkhize but I was unable to get land for a long time.“I eventually managed to get some early this year.“When I told Mkhize where it was he said he wasn’t happy. That’s why building his house has been delayed.”However, Mkhize denied Madonda’s claims. He said: “No one ever came to me after Zuma’s visit. He is lying when he says he told me about the land and that I didn’t like it.”Zuma’s spokesman Bongani Ngqulunga said: “I’ll check all the facts when the president is finished at the conference.”Disable man Mbuso Mkhize's mud house. He said President Jacob Zuma promised him a decent house four years ago.
